What you need to know:

Post-World War II period saw Britain put more pressure on her colonies, including Kenya, to intensify production to reduce dependence on fruit imports from the US.The quantities of pineapple exports increased during the 1950s. In 1954, 2,163 acres were under pineapple growing in Kiambu. Smallholders in Kiambu and Murang’a experienced unprecedented losses and turned to either tea or coffee.The fruits are grown in Kericho (Belgut), Nandi, Bungoma, Nyamira (Ikonge) and Homa Bay (Kochia and formerly Kabondo) without essential extension services. 